\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Floor, identity, and purpose.} \textbf  {(Top, A--D)} Every boundary cost $b(U)$ lands on or above the floor line, its histogram is supported on $b(U)/\beta \ge 1$ with the minimum at $1.010$, the character invariant $\chi $ is fixed on the diagonal under relabelling, and (3D) $\chi $ of the two-triangle agent tracks the \emph  {join} weight, not the triangle weight---identity is where the cheap cut is. \textbf  {(Bottom, A--D)} Convergence trajectories fall under the $e^{-\lambda t}$ envelope, the empirical return rate matches $\lambda $ on the diagonal, the 2D flow has a single fixed point (the purpose), and the strongly convex drive surface has a unique minimiser.}}{14}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
