\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Society and crowd.} \textbf  {(Top, A--D)} The society realised floor stays strictly positive as the number of agents grows; the two-cluster society's $\chi $ follows the join weight while every singleton cut is dearer; collective failure $\DOTSB \prod@ \slimits@ _i q_i$ decays geometrically in the crowd size $n$ for each failure level; and (3D) the failure surface over $(n,q)$ collapses toward zero. \textbf  {(Bottom, A--D)} Disjoint agents' outcomes cluster inside the shared tolerance cell; the reachable fraction rises with crowd size; committed-count trajectories of a fresh copy and its original never meet (copies stay distinct forever); and the committed record is strictly monotone even across revisited positions.}}{15}{figure.caption.4}\protected@file@percent }
